1
00:00:26,526 --> 00:00:29,070
Mr. Hwang Johan, you're free to go.

2
00:00:30,238 --> 00:00:31,948
Please check your belongings.

3
00:00:38,621 --> 00:00:39,998
Is everything there?

4
00:00:40,081 --> 00:00:41,082
Yes.

5
00:00:42,208 --> 00:00:43,626
Wait a second.

6
00:00:51,342 --> 00:00:53,053
You should wear this for a while.

7
00:00:56,473 --> 00:00:57,474
Okay.

8
00:01:12,113 --> 00:01:14,074
MISSED CALL FROM SUA
MISSED CALL FROM RYU

9
00:01:14,157 --> 00:01:15,283
SUA: PLEASE PICK UP

10
00:01:15,366 --> 00:01:16,826
RYU: ARE YOU OKAY? PLEASE REPLY

11
00:01:16,910 --> 00:01:17,786
CALLING RYU

12
00:01:29,005 --> 00:01:32,092
<i>The person you are trying to reach</i>
<i>is unavailable.</i>

13
00:01:32,175 --> 00:01:34,511
<i>Please leave your message…</i>

14
00:01:37,931 --> 00:01:39,390
What should we eat today?

15
00:01:40,183 --> 00:01:41,184
Today?

16
00:01:41,810 --> 00:01:44,646
Hey, did you see this?

17
00:01:44,729 --> 00:01:45,730
What?

18
00:01:47,107 --> 00:01:51,402
A pro boxer beat someone up
and got released? That's crazy.

19
00:01:51,903 --> 00:01:54,572
A civilian could die
if they're hit by a professional.

20
00:01:54,656 --> 00:01:58,243
I saw on the news
that he even threw his fights.

21
00:01:58,326 --> 00:02:00,245
-Threw fights?
-Yeah.

22
00:02:02,163 --> 00:02:05,458
Why would the police release
someone like that?

23
00:02:05,542 --> 00:02:07,961
That’s why they get criticized
all the time.

24
00:02:08,044 --> 00:02:09,087
So true.

25
00:02:32,861 --> 00:02:36,573
GAY BASTARD

26
00:02:51,171 --> 00:02:54,174
KANG SUNGMIN BOXING GYM

27
00:03:02,724 --> 00:03:03,725
Johan.

28
00:03:05,310 --> 00:03:06,144
You're here.

29
00:03:14,819 --> 00:03:16,404
Why are you here, Johan?

30
00:03:17,405 --> 00:03:18,281
Jisub.

31
00:03:18,364 --> 00:03:20,617
This place is going under because of you.

32
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:21,743
That's enough.

33
00:03:25,288 --> 00:03:27,707
Don't worry about it. It's fine.

34
00:03:27,790 --> 00:03:30,084
No, it's not!

35
00:03:30,168 --> 00:03:32,378
I said it's fine!

36
00:03:35,632 --> 00:03:37,967
Do you have any idea
what he's been through?

37
00:03:40,345 --> 00:03:41,554
Coach.

38
00:03:41,638 --> 00:03:43,056
Are you for real?

39
00:03:43,139 --> 00:03:44,807
You still call him "Coach"?

40
00:03:44,891 --> 00:03:47,560
You hit a civilian and even fixed matches.

41
00:03:48,061 --> 00:03:50,271
The association wouldn't let this slide.

42
00:03:50,355 --> 00:03:51,648
Let go.

43
00:03:51,731 --> 00:03:53,483
-Well?
-I said let go!

44
00:03:55,235 --> 00:03:56,903
That's enough.

45
00:03:56,986 --> 00:03:58,446
You can go home now.

46
00:04:12,835 --> 00:04:14,170
Sorry.

47
00:04:15,255 --> 00:04:16,673
That's what happened.

48
00:04:18,591 --> 00:04:21,177
I won't be able to employ you anymore.

49
00:04:23,179 --> 00:04:25,723
It's all my fault.

50
00:04:27,183 --> 00:04:30,019
This was all Shim's doing.

51
00:04:30,937 --> 00:04:33,815
And my way of doing things
is old-fashioned

52
00:04:34,607 --> 00:04:36,276
and outdated.

53
00:04:38,194 --> 00:04:40,154
You used to say that a lot too.

54
00:04:49,497 --> 00:04:52,458
I remember the first time you came here.

55
00:04:53,167 --> 00:04:54,711
I enjoyed

56
00:04:56,587 --> 00:05:01,926
getting to box with you.

57
00:05:08,057 --> 00:05:09,767
Don't push yourself too hard

58
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:12,395
and take it easy in life.

59
00:05:13,980 --> 00:05:15,106
Got it?

60
00:05:23,031 --> 00:05:26,409
MISSED CALL FROM JOHAN

61
00:05:26,492 --> 00:05:27,618
Ryu, got a minute?

62
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:30,455
Yes.

63
00:05:30,538 --> 00:05:32,665
We have an emergency admission tomorrow.

64
00:05:32,749 --> 00:05:34,375
Can you help me prepare?

65
00:05:34,876 --> 00:05:36,461
Got it.

66
00:05:41,716 --> 00:05:44,302
You loser!
I'll destroy everything important to you!

67
00:06:11,954 --> 00:06:13,289
<i>I'm not a loser.</i>

68
00:06:13,373 --> 00:06:15,166
I'm not a loser dog!

69
00:06:18,419 --> 00:06:19,629
I trust you.

70
00:06:19,712 --> 00:06:23,007
The way you never gave up
made you look stronger than anyone else.

71
00:06:23,091 --> 00:06:24,300
Go, Johan!

72
00:06:25,051 --> 00:06:27,220
It's always been just the two of us.

73
00:06:28,930 --> 00:06:30,848
-The soul.
-The soul?

74
00:06:30,932 --> 00:06:32,225
I'll protect it.

75
00:06:32,725 --> 00:06:36,521
To make that happen,
I'm going to destroy it.

76
00:06:45,154 --> 00:06:48,741
Why is it always me?!

77
00:07:02,630 --> 00:07:05,633
<i>We have connected your call,</i>
<i>but there was no answer.</i>

78
00:07:05,716 --> 00:07:08,177
<i>Please leave a message after the tone.</i>

79
00:07:33,369 --> 00:07:34,954
-<i>Ryu?</i>
-Oh, hello?

80
00:07:35,037 --> 00:07:36,414
Sorry for the sudden call.

81
00:07:37,373 --> 00:07:38,583
<i>What should I do?</i>

82
00:07:38,666 --> 00:07:40,877
Is Johan…

83
00:07:41,544 --> 00:07:43,004
<i>Johan is…</i>

84
00:07:45,423 --> 00:07:47,717
I've been calling him all this time.

85
00:07:48,885 --> 00:07:49,969
I, um…

86
00:07:50,052 --> 00:07:51,012
It'll be fine.

87
00:07:51,512 --> 00:07:54,348
Let's start with places
where we might find a lead.

88
00:07:54,974 --> 00:07:56,517
Yes.

89
00:07:56,601 --> 00:07:57,810
It'll be fine.

90
00:07:57,894 --> 00:08:00,480
We'll find him for sure.

91
00:08:00,563 --> 00:08:01,856
We will.

92
00:08:02,356 --> 00:08:04,984
Yes. Thank you.

93
00:08:05,067 --> 00:08:12,074
GAY BASTARD

94
00:08:17,121 --> 00:08:20,583
Johan!

95
00:09:16,597 --> 00:09:18,558
OUR DOORS WILL CLOSE ON APRIL 30TH

96
00:09:18,641 --> 00:09:20,643
It looks like they've shut down.

97
00:09:27,483 --> 00:09:29,360
What about the bar where it happened?

98
00:09:30,361 --> 00:09:31,821
Do you know where it is?

99
00:09:32,697 --> 00:09:33,698
Yes.

100
00:09:35,491 --> 00:09:36,534
I do.

101
00:09:45,751 --> 00:09:46,752
Which way?

102
00:09:46,836 --> 00:09:48,588
-It's this way.
-This way?

103
00:10:06,188 --> 00:10:07,982
You're Johan's little sister?

104
00:10:08,816 --> 00:10:09,984
Yes.

105
00:10:13,654 --> 00:10:16,490
Then are you perhaps Ryu?

106
00:10:18,409 --> 00:10:19,410
Ryu.

107
00:10:25,875 --> 00:10:28,085
Johan's told me a lot about you two.

108
00:10:29,003 --> 00:10:30,921
I didn't expect to meet you like this.

109
00:10:39,430 --> 00:10:41,015
Excuse me.

110
00:10:41,599 --> 00:10:43,225
Do you know where my brother is?

111
00:10:47,396 --> 00:10:53,444
Please tell us… where Johan is.

112
00:10:54,403 --> 00:10:55,988
Please.

113
00:10:56,572 --> 00:11:00,910
He told me not to tell anyone,
even if you two came here.

114
00:11:02,536 --> 00:11:05,206
Please, I'm begging you!

115
00:11:05,289 --> 00:11:07,333
Please stop.

116
00:11:07,416 --> 00:11:08,751
I'm begging you.

117
00:11:09,377 --> 00:11:10,795
Please don't do this.

118
00:11:12,338 --> 00:11:13,839
That kid…

119
00:11:17,385 --> 00:11:18,844
Please save him.

120
00:11:20,763 --> 00:11:23,766
<i>I think he's at the abandoned factory</i>
<i>where he used to work.</i>

121
00:11:24,642 --> 00:11:27,937
<i>He said that's the only place left</i>
<i>where he can work.</i>

122
00:11:28,813 --> 00:11:30,523
-Thank you.
-Take care.

123
00:11:30,606 --> 00:11:31,816
Thank you.

124
00:11:53,170 --> 00:11:59,135
NO TRESPASSING

125
00:12:09,895 --> 00:12:13,065
Johan!

126
00:12:14,442 --> 00:12:15,484
Open the door!

127
00:12:15,568 --> 00:12:17,737
-Johan!
-Johan!

128
00:12:47,308 --> 00:12:49,226
That's Johan's manga.

129
00:12:49,310 --> 00:12:50,311
Yeah.

130
00:13:02,865 --> 00:13:04,325
Johan!

131
00:13:04,408 --> 00:13:05,826
-Johan!
-Johan!

132
00:13:16,420 --> 00:13:17,254
Hey, wait!

133
00:13:24,053 --> 00:13:25,304
Johan!

134
00:13:36,899 --> 00:13:39,485
You're getting out of shape, huh?

135
00:13:40,653 --> 00:13:42,905
Why did you come here?

136
00:13:52,832 --> 00:13:57,294
Just leave me alone.

137
00:13:57,962 --> 00:14:00,089
You want me to leave you alone?

138
00:14:02,550 --> 00:14:03,884
Don't you get it?

139
00:14:05,761 --> 00:14:07,054
It's…

140
00:14:08,597 --> 00:14:10,099
It's all over for me now.

141
00:14:12,184 --> 00:14:14,270
If you get involved with me…

142
00:14:17,731 --> 00:14:22,152
bad things will happen to you too.

143
00:14:32,663 --> 00:14:34,290
Why are you laughing?

144
00:14:40,629 --> 00:14:42,548
You were trying to protect it, right?

145
00:14:47,553 --> 00:14:49,054
Your soul.

146
00:15:31,305 --> 00:15:32,514
You're…

147
00:15:33,641 --> 00:15:37,978
You're the one person
I didn't want to see me like this.

148
00:15:52,534 --> 00:15:53,535
Johan.

149
00:15:58,666 --> 00:16:01,669
Let's live together in Japan.

150
00:16:57,266 --> 00:16:59,268
Let's eat.

151
00:17:07,860 --> 00:17:09,319
<i>Masisseo</i>.

152
00:17:11,739 --> 00:17:13,032
This is good!

153
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:36,138
Earlier…

154
00:17:38,057 --> 00:17:39,058
Hm?

155
00:17:42,019 --> 00:17:44,730
You mentioned living together in Japan.

156
00:17:46,857 --> 00:17:47,983
Did you mean it?

157
00:17:49,651 --> 00:17:50,652
Oh.

158
00:17:53,447 --> 00:17:54,448
Yeah.

159
00:17:56,116 --> 00:17:56,950
I meant it.

160
00:18:22,267 --> 00:18:23,268
I…

161
00:18:25,604 --> 00:18:27,231
have a dream.

162
00:18:27,731 --> 00:18:28,732
Hm?

163
00:18:32,361 --> 00:18:34,321
I want to go to university

164
00:18:35,948 --> 00:18:36,782
in Japan.

165
00:18:40,077 --> 00:18:41,078
Yeah.

166
00:18:42,412 --> 00:18:43,413
Good idea.

167
00:18:55,300 --> 00:18:56,468
Thank you

168
00:18:57,719 --> 00:18:59,346
for coming.

169
00:19:02,349 --> 00:19:03,183
What'd you say?

170
00:19:10,440 --> 00:19:11,441
I won't say it again.

171
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:48,896
"Anyway, in life,

172
00:19:49,980 --> 00:19:56,737
it is better to spend your time
doing what you enjoy."

173
00:20:09,166 --> 00:20:10,709
I'm home.

174
00:20:10,792 --> 00:20:12,085
Welcome back.

175
00:20:17,132 --> 00:20:20,594
Whoa, this looks so good.

176
00:20:21,303 --> 00:20:22,596
Wow.

177
00:20:24,306 --> 00:20:26,558
Wash your hands first.

178
00:20:27,351 --> 00:20:29,186
-Yeah, okay.
-Yeah.

179
00:20:31,897 --> 00:20:35,108
-Oh, help yourself to rice.
-Okay.

180
00:20:35,192 --> 00:20:36,026
Yeah.

181
00:20:42,658 --> 00:20:43,700
Stop moving.

182
00:20:45,202 --> 00:20:48,038
It's impossible to eat without moving.

183
00:20:52,668 --> 00:20:56,797
I'm going to a farewell party
for the head of the caretaker department,

184
00:20:56,880 --> 00:20:58,715
so I don't need dinner tomorrow.

185
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:01,551
Oh, I see.

186
00:21:02,636 --> 00:21:05,305
Mmm. This is good.

187
00:21:06,807 --> 00:21:08,517
Of course it is.

188
00:21:14,273 --> 00:21:18,902
Hey, are you free this weekend
to meet with Sumiko and Seiichi?

189
00:21:19,403 --> 00:21:21,154
Yeah, I'm free.

190
00:21:22,072 --> 00:21:25,117
I have no plans other than my shift
at the convenience store.

191
00:21:28,161 --> 00:21:31,415
I hope you get to work
at the Korean language school.

192
00:21:31,498 --> 00:21:33,417
Easier said than done.

193
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:36,003
It's difficult without a degree.

194
00:21:40,007 --> 00:21:42,050
I gotta study
for my caregiver training too.

195
00:21:42,134 --> 00:21:43,552
Don't just move like that.

196
00:21:43,635 --> 00:21:45,137
I'm getting seconds.

197
00:21:46,555 --> 00:21:47,556
Okay, then.

198
00:21:59,276 --> 00:22:01,361
-He's good.
-Johan's amazing!

199
00:22:03,113 --> 00:22:05,741
Come on, jump!

200
00:22:05,824 --> 00:22:08,535
Wait. Let's take a break.

201
00:22:08,618 --> 00:22:10,120
I give up.

202
00:22:10,954 --> 00:22:13,373
Is it your arm? Or maybe it's the snap?

203
00:22:13,457 --> 00:22:15,208
Yeah, it's all in the snap.

204
00:22:15,917 --> 00:22:17,336
Water, please.

205
00:22:17,419 --> 00:22:18,337
I'm no match.

206
00:22:18,420 --> 00:22:19,254
-Here.
-Here.

207
00:22:19,338 --> 00:22:20,756
-Oh, thanks.
-Thanks.

208
00:22:20,839 --> 00:22:22,716
-You're way too tired.
-I'm beat.

209
00:22:22,799 --> 00:22:24,092
All right.

210
00:22:24,593 --> 00:22:25,802
-Then…
-Then…

211
00:22:25,886 --> 00:22:27,137
If you please.

212
00:22:27,220 --> 00:22:28,847
If you please.

213
00:22:30,724 --> 00:22:33,060
All right, my junior, you write.

214
00:22:33,143 --> 00:22:35,437
You need me to write it first.

215
00:22:36,104 --> 00:22:37,814
-Okay, I'm filling it in.
-Okay.

216
00:22:37,898 --> 00:22:39,232
All right.

217
00:22:39,733 --> 00:22:40,817
I'll stamp it.

218
00:22:40,901 --> 00:22:42,402
-Yes, please.
-Yes, please.

219
00:22:42,486 --> 00:22:45,614
HWANG JOHAN

220
00:22:45,697 --> 00:22:47,949
-Wow.
-Wow.

221
00:22:49,993 --> 00:22:51,244
All right.

222
00:22:52,871 --> 00:22:53,789
I'll stamp it.

223
00:22:53,872 --> 00:22:55,082
Yes, please.

224
00:22:55,165 --> 00:22:59,795
RYU NARUTAKI

225
00:22:59,878 --> 00:23:01,838
-Yeah.
-Wow.

226
00:23:01,922 --> 00:23:03,048
Thank you.

227
00:23:03,632 --> 00:23:04,674
-Congrats.
-Congrats.

228
00:23:04,758 --> 00:23:06,218
Thank you, both of you.

229
00:23:06,885 --> 00:23:08,595
I'm so glad.

230
00:23:09,888 --> 00:23:11,890
Wow, it's nice. Neat writing.

231
00:23:12,766 --> 00:23:17,479
Man, it feels special
having you sign this, Ryu.

232
00:23:18,146 --> 00:23:19,689
That's my line.

233
00:23:20,816 --> 00:23:22,109
Thank you too, Johan.

234
00:23:22,192 --> 00:23:23,026
It's nothing.

235
00:23:28,115 --> 00:23:29,449
Guess what?

236
00:23:30,367 --> 00:23:31,368
Hm?

237
00:23:35,122 --> 00:23:36,373
We're expecting.

238
00:23:38,500 --> 00:23:39,501
Huh?

239
00:23:44,131 --> 00:23:45,132
A baby.

240
00:23:49,219 --> 00:23:50,137
What?!

241
00:23:51,847 --> 00:23:53,098
-Seriously?
-Yeah.

242
00:23:53,181 --> 00:23:54,307
Yeah.

243
00:23:54,391 --> 00:23:55,392
Up we go.

244
00:23:55,892 --> 00:23:56,893
Congrats, Sumiko.

245
00:23:57,644 --> 00:23:58,562
Thank you.

246
00:23:58,645 --> 00:24:00,021
Congratulations.

247
00:24:02,232 --> 00:24:06,528
I had bad morning sickness,
but I'm feeling better now.

248
00:24:07,863 --> 00:24:11,032
We wanted to tell you guys in person.

249
00:24:11,533 --> 00:24:12,367
I see.

250
00:24:12,451 --> 00:24:13,743
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

251
00:24:16,455 --> 00:24:17,914
In that case…

252
00:24:20,834 --> 00:24:22,294
Can I feel it?

253
00:24:23,879 --> 00:24:24,880
Of course.

254
00:24:26,548 --> 00:24:28,216
Hey, you don't have to do that.

255
00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:30,969
No, no. All right.

256
00:24:38,768 --> 00:24:41,771
-Whoa.
-What?

257
00:24:42,397 --> 00:24:43,565
-Wow.
-Huh?

258
00:24:43,648 --> 00:24:45,650
-Wow!
-What is it?

259
00:24:46,568 --> 00:24:47,402
You try too.

260
00:24:47,486 --> 00:24:49,070
-Wait, can I?
-Yeah.

261
00:24:51,114 --> 00:24:52,365
-Excuse me.
-Go ahead.

262
00:24:56,870 --> 00:24:57,913
-Whoa.
-Right?

263
00:24:57,996 --> 00:24:58,830
Yeah.

264
00:24:59,873 --> 00:25:00,916
What was that?

265
00:25:00,999 --> 00:25:02,000
-Right?
-Yeah.

266
00:25:02,083 --> 00:25:02,918
Man.

267
00:25:03,001 --> 00:25:05,962
Wow, there's a baby in here, huh?

268
00:25:06,046 --> 00:25:07,047
Yeah.

269
00:25:08,632 --> 00:25:11,510
All right. You're up next, Ryu.

270
00:25:11,593 --> 00:25:13,178
-Huh?
-Huh?

271
00:25:13,678 --> 00:25:18,391
I couldn't beat you at ice hockey,
but I won't lose at this.

272
00:25:18,475 --> 00:25:19,726
Come on, let's do this.

273
00:25:19,809 --> 00:25:21,561
What? We're still playing?

274
00:25:21,645 --> 00:25:24,439
Of course. Come on, move it!

275
00:25:24,523 --> 00:25:26,775
-We were talking here.
-No, let's play.

276
00:25:26,858 --> 00:25:27,817
Come on.

277
00:25:27,901 --> 00:25:29,611
-Have fun!
-Ugh, jeez.

278
00:25:29,694 --> 00:25:32,822
-Hey, run. Let's go!
-I don't wanna.

279
00:25:32,906 --> 00:25:34,241
-Go!
-Jeez!

280
00:25:34,741 --> 00:25:36,952
What? Is he playing by himself?

281
00:25:37,035 --> 00:25:38,578
Ready? Here!

282
00:25:38,662 --> 00:25:41,039
-It came right back at you.
-Come on! Run!

283
00:25:49,548 --> 00:25:51,049
About Ryu…

284
00:25:54,135 --> 00:25:55,512
Take care of him, okay?

285
00:26:02,435 --> 00:26:03,645
Leave him to me.

286
00:26:07,649 --> 00:26:09,651
You gotta jump!

287
00:26:12,404 --> 00:26:13,989
Wasn't that amazing?

288
00:26:14,948 --> 00:26:15,949
What was?

289
00:26:16,825 --> 00:26:20,912
I was just thinking how amazing
Seiichi and Sumiko are.

290
00:26:20,996 --> 00:26:22,038
Hmm.

291
00:26:22,122 --> 00:26:24,040
They're having a kid.

292
00:26:25,375 --> 00:26:26,376
Yeah.

293
00:26:34,718 --> 00:26:38,388
Do you want kids too?

294
00:26:39,598 --> 00:26:42,559
Hmm. Kids, huh?

295
00:26:43,059 --> 00:26:45,020
I've never really thought about it.

296
00:26:47,731 --> 00:26:49,649
-I see.
-Yeah.

297
00:26:52,986 --> 00:26:56,197
But it definitely felt like a miracle.

298
00:27:06,833 --> 00:27:08,251
A miracle.

299
00:27:08,918 --> 00:27:09,919
Yeah.

300
00:27:15,884 --> 00:27:18,637
The fact that I'm here is a miracle too.

301
00:27:19,346 --> 00:27:20,347
Hm?

302
00:27:22,432 --> 00:27:25,518
I just happened to meet you in Germany.

303
00:27:26,936 --> 00:27:28,271
And right now, somehow…

304
00:27:30,315 --> 00:27:33,234
we're living together in Japan.

305
00:27:38,865 --> 00:27:40,241
It's a miracle, isn't it?

306
00:27:41,242 --> 00:27:42,243
That's true.

307
00:27:44,996 --> 00:27:46,164
It's a miracle.

308
00:27:56,174 --> 00:27:57,425
All right.

309
00:27:58,885 --> 00:27:59,928
I'm off.

310
00:28:00,011 --> 00:28:01,429
Okay. Have a good day.

311
00:28:03,390 --> 00:28:04,683
I'm off.

312
00:28:04,766 --> 00:28:06,810
"Have a good day."

313
00:28:09,020 --> 00:28:11,606
-Call me if anything happens.
-I will.

314
00:28:13,149 --> 00:28:16,027
-Promise.
-I know. I will.

315
00:28:16,111 --> 00:28:17,737
-Okay, see you later.
-See you.

316
00:28:17,821 --> 00:28:19,197
-Be careful.
-Okay.

317
00:28:19,280 --> 00:28:26,287
HAPPY NAME DICTIONARY FOR BABIES

318
00:28:29,749 --> 00:28:32,085
-Phew.
-Hey, watch your back!

319
00:28:32,168 --> 00:28:33,920
-I'm fine.
-Isn't it heavy?

320
00:28:34,003 --> 00:28:36,798
Not at all.
Remember, I'm Super Scrappy Seiichi!

321
00:28:36,881 --> 00:28:37,841
Hey, over here.

322
00:28:37,924 --> 00:28:39,551
-Yes.
-Bring out that thing.

323
00:28:39,634 --> 00:28:40,760
Okay.

324
00:28:41,845 --> 00:28:43,346
There we go.

325
00:28:45,598 --> 00:28:46,975
-This here…
-Yes?

326
00:28:47,058 --> 00:28:51,771
We know it's a bit late,
but this one's from us.

327
00:28:52,439 --> 00:28:53,982
A wedding gift.

328
00:28:54,065 --> 00:28:57,527
-What? No way. Really?
-Yeah.

329
00:28:57,610 --> 00:29:00,405
And your baby's coming soon too.
How exciting.

330
00:29:01,281 --> 00:29:03,408
Yes. Thank you very much.

331
00:29:05,952 --> 00:29:07,537
Well, then. Goodbye.

332
00:31:39,814 --> 00:31:42,734
Subtitle translation by: Remi Miura
